metadata.title: SSA State Agency Disability Determination Workload Data
metadata.description: Comprehensive disability determination workload data from the Social Security Administration (SSA). Includes state-level data on initial disability claims (Title II DI and Title XVI SSI), favorable/unfavorable determination rates, DDS accuracy rates, processing times, and disability prevalence by state. Covers adult (age 18-64) and child (under 18) populations.
metadata.source: U.S. Social Security Administration (SSA) - Office of Disability Determinations
metadata.fetch_method: Wayback Machine archive (SSA blocks direct server-side requests as of 2025+)
metadata.methodology: Data downloaded from SSA Open Data portal via Wayback Machine cache. SSA-SA-FYWL contains state agency fiscal year workload data for disability determinations under Title II (Disability Insurance) and Title XVI (Supplemental Security Income). Adult population = ages 18-64; child population = under 18. Eligible population = total population minus current beneficiaries. Favorable determinations = initial disability claims approved by DDS. Filing rate = receipts / eligible population. Allowance rate = favorable determinations / all determinations.

programs_covered.Title II (DI): Social Security Disability Insurance - for workers with sufficient work history who become disabled
programs_covered.Title XVI (SSI): Supplemental Security Income - for disabled individuals with limited income/resources, including children

key_terms.DDS: Disability Determination Services - state agencies that make initial disability decisions for SSA
key_terms.CDR: Continuing Disability Review - periodic review of beneficiaries to check if they remain disabled
key_terms.Favorable Determination: Claim approved/allowed (claimant found to be disabled)
key_terms.Unfavorable Determination: Claim denied (claimant not found to be disabled at this level)
key_terms.Reconsideration: First level of appeal after initial denial
key_terms.Filing Rate: Percentage of eligible population filing disability claims
key_terms.Allowance Rate: Percentage of determinations that are favorable (approved)

datasets_included.fiscal_year_workload: SSA State Agency Fiscal Year Workload Data - disability determination statistics by state and fiscal year, including adult and child populations, receipts, determinations, and allowance rates
datasets_included.dds_accuracy: Disability Determination Services (DDS) Net Accuracy Rate by state and fiscal year
datasets_included.processing_time_title_xvi: Title XVI Blind/Disabled Average Processing Time (In Days)
datasets_included.recon_processing_time: Disability Reconsideration Average Processing Time (In Days)
